deck: Student With a Magic Wish-Granting Brooch
description:
Origin

One evening Maisie witnessed a falling meteorite land nearby her house, being an avid Jewelry maker she searched out the Meteorite and broke off a piece, deciding to make it into a Brooch

The next day Maisie learned that if the Brooch was glowing everything she said would actually happen, whether an inadvertently made off-hand comment or not, but the power would randomly come and go.

Creation

Maisie was created for the Girl's comic Sally, appearing right from the first issue. After Sally was cancelled and merged with Tammy the character lived on in that comic.
name: Maisie Macrae

deck: Cunning Gotham bank robber armed with sophisticated weaponry and toxins.
description:
Appearing first in the 1960s live action Batman TV series, the Black Widow was an Auntie-Mame-like character created specifically for Miss Tallulah Bankhead, the colorful grand dame of stage and film (in real life, the actress was renowned for throwing wild parties that lasted days and at one time owned a pet lion).

Some of the Black Widow's devices include a robot senior citizen rocking on a porch and a mind control device. Even after she is arrested, she continues to mesmerize men with her self-assurance and flamboyance, convincing Chief O'Hara to provide her with a wine list (and menu) for her prison dinner.

The episode has one of the more ethically uncomfortable presentations of the live action TV Batman:

When the Black Widow is arrested at the end of the episode, Batman uses her own mind control device on her, then has the mind-controlled Black Widow waive her Miranda rights, and later at the Gotham City prison, he uses a mind control device disguised as a hair dryer to alter her mind to a law-abiding one.
name: Black Widow

deck: Protagonist of the video game series of the same name. Cereza is the Daughter of an Umbran Witch and Lumen Sage, part of the two clans that over look the world from the darkness and light. After 500 years the Umbran Witches were destroyed and Cereza was put to sleep for five hundred years until awoken. With no memories of who she is she sets out killing Angel's under the alias: Bayonetta.
description:
Origin

Cereza is the Daughter of a Lumen Sage and an Umbran Witch, two powerful beings from separate clans: The Lumen Sages that serve under Paradiso/Heaven, and the Umbran Wtitches who work with Inferno/Hell. Her birth brought open an age old phrophecy that would cause the destruction of the world. Her Mother was imprisoned and her Father was banished while Cereza was dubbed the Black Sheep among the Witches. During her older years her clan was attacked by Angels and Sages that was known as the Witch Hunts. Later her friend/rival Jeanne put Cereza into a sleep for the next five hundred years, waking up with no memories of who she was. She would then take on a name that is feared by the Angels with her Demons and contract Demon Madamma Butterfly as her alias: Bayonetta.

First Game

Bayonetta goes to the city of Vigrid to uncover the truth of her past, and discover of the Left Eye. During her time there she learns Vigrid was the stronghold for both the Lumen Sages and Umbran Witches. She then encounters the Cardinal Virtue of Fortitude: Fortitudo, the Bringer of Flame. After defeating the Cardinal she encounters a little girl by the name of Cereza. The little girl travels with Bayonetta as they come across the other Cardinal Virtues: Temperance, Prudence, and Justice and slayed everyone. She encountered Jeanne as well who was under the control of the Lumen Sage: Balder, the last Lumen Sage and the cause of the Witch Hunts. He revealed to Bayonetta that he is the cause for everything, he brought Cereza who is in fact a younger version of Bayonetta since she saw the world through pure eyes. By doing this she would charge the Left eye and the Right eye to recreate the Eyes of the World: Sacred powers given by the Lumen Sages and Umbran Witches, to reawaken the Creator Jubileus. However Jeanne, after being freed from the control, freed Bayonetta before Jubileus could be awaken. The lost of the Left eye caused Jubileus to become incomplete and soon attack Bayonetta to take back the eye. After a long hard battle Bayonetta and Jeanne summon Queen Sheba, the ruler of Inferno to deliver the final blow that sent Jubileus spirit into the Sun. Her statue however was soon crumbling to the Earth, causing Bayonetta and Jeanne to work together to destroy it. They destroyed the statue and soon landed on Earth. However many believed Bayonetta to be dead as Rodin, her Weapons dealer and Enzo, and Luka: A journalist who once had a grudge against Bayonetta for her killing his father before he learned Balder did it. They attended her grave site before Angel's appeared and attacked, revealing it was a ruse and Bayonetta was alive and back to kick butt.

Bayonetta 2

Sometime after the death of Jubileus as well as Balder and the Right Eye Bayonetta is doing some Christmas shopping. However she is soon attacked by Angels, she fought them throughout the entire city before she summoned Gomorrah to kill all the Angels. However the summoning fails and Gomorrah breaks free to attack Bayonetta, but at the last second Jeanne takes the blow. This however blasted her soul out of her body allowing the demons to drag her down in Inferno.
name: Bayonetta

deck: Kintaro Oe is a twenty-five-year-old in pursuit of life's lessons
description: A brilliant student, he dropped out of Tokyo Universiy's law program because he had had mastered the entire curriculum. Now he lives a simple life, traveling on his bicycle and working numerous part-time jobs ranging from software companies to noodle restaurants in order to learn everything that he can about the world. Although he's a kind and giving person, Kintaro's only weakness lies in his lust for beautiful women. However, as long as he can control himself, he may just manage to save the day.
name: Kintaro Oe

deck: Manifold Tyger is a member of the Providian Order, posing as a S.W.O.R.D. agent.
description:
Exogenous

Manifold Tyger poses as an agent of S.W.O.R.D., working under Director Abigail Brand. He works with the X-Men when they arrive at the Peak to deal with Deathbird's reappearance. He helps repair the Kirby engines and fight off the Sidrian Hunters. However, his true allegiance is later revealed. He is a member of the Providian Order, and organization dedicated to perfecting the universe by creating a race of perfect beings. To that end, Tyger was ordered to murder everyone on board the Peak.
name: Manifold Tyger

description:
Origin

Whilst on vacation with his father in Calcutta, James Hollis stopped to watch a local man doing the Indian Rope Trick. After the trick was finished the Fakir overheard James' father insulting his trick and advising James not to give the man any money for his trouble. The Fakir decided to curse James' father to become a man made of rubber, but accidentally cursed James instead.

When the two got back home James' dad was murdered by men working for a rival company, James himself then learned that he had gained the ability to stretch his body and resolved to catch the killers.

Creation

Rubberman was created for Odhams' comic, Smash, first appearing in its 15th Issue in 1966.

Powers

Rubberman can stretch and warp his body, bullets bounce off him and he is resistant to blunt impacts.
name: Rubberman
